SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1032
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Kehilla Upper School of
Nashville.
WHEREAS, Kehilla Upper School of Nashville emerged in response to a longstanding
gap in the Jewish educational system within the City of Nashville, where families historically had
access to Jewish elementary education through Akiva School but lacked local options for upper-
level Jewish day school education; and
WHEREAS, for many years, families seeking continued Jewish education beyond the
sixth grade were often required to relocate to larger cities due to the prevailing assumption that
a full upper-school program was not sustainable within a community of Nashville's size; and
WHEREAS, a group of educators and community leaders sought to address this need
by establishing the Jewish Middle School of Nashville (JMS), representing an initial effort to
extend Jewish education beyond the elementary level; and
WHEREAS, the success and growth of JMS demonstrated both community demand and
program viability, ultimately leading to its expansion into a high school program now known as
Kehilla Upper School; and
WHEREAS, Kehilla Upper School provides advanced Judaic and rabbinic studies while
also welcoming students from diverse faith backgrounds, offering education grounded in Judeo-
Christian values and including instruction in the Hebrew language; and
WHEREAS, the establishment of Kehilla Upper School created, for the first time in
Nashville, a continuous local Jewish day school educational pathway from early childhood
through secondary education; and
SJR1032
016725
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the institution has developed a reputation for delivering rigorous college-
preparatory academics alongside faith-based learning within a student-centered environment,
including experiential learning opportunities, such as a senior-year trip to Israel; and
WHEREAS, Kehilla Upper School currently serves students in grades seven through
twelve and provides a comprehensive educational experience that integrates intellectual
development, personal identity, character formation, and civic responsibility; and
WHEREAS, the school has evolved into a significant institution within the Nashville
community, contributing to the sustainability and growth of Jewish secondary education in the
region; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Kehilla Upper School of
Nashville for its significant contributions to education and community development and extend
our best wishes for its continued success in the years to come.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
